# Coding standards (reflex)

TypeScript / Biome / Vitest / pnpm-workspace reflexes. For procedural how-tos see
`.copilot/skills/`; for surgical, scope-specific rules see the sibling files in `.agents/rules/`
(`core-no-framework.md`, `tests-co-located.md`, `progress-on-package-edit.md`,
`harness-on-architectural-change.md`, `no-debug-logging.md`, `security.md`, `code-review.md`).

- **Smallest fix that fully solves the problem.** Do not refactor unrelated code or "improve
  while you're here". Diff scope is a graded review axis.
- **Match Biome formatting** (`pnpm lint` â†’ `biome check .`): 2-space indent, single quotes,
  trailing commas everywhere, semicolons always, 100-char lines, arrow parens always. Run
  `pnpm lint:fix` for the 95% that auto-fixes; never introduce a different formatter.
- **TypeScript is strict mode** (`tsconfig.base.json`): `noUncheckedIndexedAccess` is on â€”
  handle the `| undefined` you get from array / `Record` access. `verbatimModuleSyntax` is on â€”
  match the surrounding file's `import` / `export` style. Avoid `as any`; if you must,
  comment why.
- **Co-locate tests.** `parse.ts` â†” `parse.test.ts` in the same directory. No `__tests__/`
  folders. Vitest only.
- **Tests import from sibling source modules** (`from './parse.js'`), never from the public
  barrel (`from '@doidor/markbook-core'`). This is what makes the `index.ts` vs `internal.ts`
  API split enforceable.
- **Public API is `index.ts` only.** New exports default to `internal.ts`. Promoting an export
  to `index.ts` is an ADR-level decision and gets a `DECISIONS.md` entry plus a `PROGRESS.md`
  line in the same commit.
- **No framework imports in `packages/core/src/**`.** No `react`, `vue`, `lit`, etc. â€” expose
  new framework behaviour as a field on `MarkbookAdapter` instead. (See `core-no-framework.md`.)
- **AST work uses the TypeScript compiler API**, not regex. Trivial scans (e.g., surfacing
  sibling CSS imports) may use regex; semantic work walks the AST.
- **In-module caches need invalidators.** Any `Map` cache in `packages/core/src/` must export
  an `invalidateXCache(absPath?)` so dev-mode HMR can wipe stale entries. The single exception
  is `htmlTemplate`'s module-level template cache (lifetime-permanent by design).
- **No `console.log` / `debugger;` / commented-out debug spew** in commits. Biome's `noConsole`
  is off because legitimate CLI output uses it â€” that is not a license to leave investigation
  prints behind.
- **No secrets in source.** Never commit npm tokens, API keys, or credentials. Publishing is
  tokenless OIDC (ADR-0029); there is no `NPM_TOKEN` and there should never be one.
- **Never disable a test, lint rule, or check** to make CI green. If a check is wrong, fix it;
  if it is right, address the underlying issue.
- **Add or update tests for behaviour you change.** One `describe` per public symbol,
  declarative `it` names, fs writes wrapped in `try/finally` rooted at `os.tmpdir()` for
  cleanup.
- **One logical change per commit.** Required co-author trailer on every commit:
  `Co-authored-by: Copilot <223556219+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>`.
- **Non-trivial `packages/**` change â†’ `PROGRESS.md` entry in the same commit** (use the
  `/progress-log` skill format). Architectural / public-API changes also update the affected
  package READMEs, the `AGENTS.md` "Where to look first" table when relevant, and an ADR in
  `DECISIONS.md` for non-obvious choices â€” all in the same commit.
- **Authoring stays simple.** Fight any change that adds config burden for the end user (a
  developer with a markdown file and a story file). KISS over expressivity.
